-- G-20 Finance Ministers to Focus on Spillover Effects in July
-- B y   S t e p a n   K r a v c h e n k o   a n d   O l g a   T a n a s
-- 2013-06-07T17:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-07/g-20-finance-ministers-to-focus-on-spillover-effects-in-july.html
G-20 may include countries’ right to
independently decide on short-term policies in July communique,
setting in writing “what is already accepted de facto,” Deputy
Finance Minister Sergei Storchak tells reporters.
* Storchak speaking after G-20 meeting of deputy finance
ministers in  St. Petersburg .
* G-20 probably won’t set debt-reduction targets at summit in
September, unlike in Toronto in 2010: Storchak
*G-20 weighing creation of tax information exchange; tax was
“about the hottest issue” at St. Petersburg meetings: Storchak  To contact the reporters on this story:
